<Link id="l00581" /><CodeLine lineNumber="581"><Highlight kind="comment">/// A function object that takes an ExecutorAddr as its first argument,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00582" /><CodeLine lineNumber="582"><Highlight kind="comment">/// casts that address to a ClassT&#42;, then calls the given method on that</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00583" /><CodeLine lineNumber="583"><Highlight kind="comment">/// pointer passing in the remaining function arguments. This utility</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00584" /><CodeLine lineNumber="584"><Highlight kind="comment">/// removes some of the boilerplate from writing wrappers for method calls.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00585" /><CodeLine lineNumber="585"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00586" /><CodeLine lineNumber="586"><Highlight kind="comment">///   @code&#123;.cpp&#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00587" /><CodeLine lineNumber="587"><Highlight kind="comment">///   class MyClass &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00588" /><CodeLine lineNumber="588"><Highlight kind="comment">///   public:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00589" /><CodeLine lineNumber="589"><Highlight kind="comment">///     void myMethod(uint32&#95;t, bool) &#123; ... &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00590" /><CodeLine lineNumber="590"><Highlight kind="comment">///   &#125;;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00591" /><CodeLine lineNumber="591"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00592" /><CodeLine lineNumber="592"><Highlight kind="comment">///   // SPS Method signature -- note MyClass object address as first argument.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00593" /><CodeLine lineNumber="593"><Highlight kind="comment">///   using SPSMyMethodWrapperSignature =</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00594" /><CodeLine lineNumber="594"><Highlight kind="comment">///     SPSTuple&lt;SPSExecutorAddr, uint32&#95;t, bool&gt;;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00595" /><CodeLine lineNumber="595"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00596" /><CodeLine lineNumber="596"><Highlight kind="comment">///   WrapperFunctionResult</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00597" /><CodeLine lineNumber="597"><Highlight kind="comment">///   myMethodCallWrapper(const char &#42;ArgData, size&#95;t ArgSize) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00598" /><CodeLine lineNumber="598"><Highlight kind="comment">///     return WrapperFunction&lt;SPSMyMethodWrapperSignature&gt;::handle(</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00599" /><CodeLine lineNumber="599"><Highlight kind="comment">///        ArgData, ArgSize, makeMethodWrapperHandler(&amp;MyClass::myMethod));</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00600" /><CodeLine lineNumber="600"><Highlight kind="comment">///   &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00601" /><CodeLine lineNumber="601"><Highlight kind="comment">///   @endcode</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00602" /><CodeLine lineNumber="602"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00603" /><CodeLine lineNumber="603"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">template</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &lt;</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">typename</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> RetT, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">typename</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> ClassT, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">typename</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">... ArgTs&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00623" /><CodeLine lineNumber="623"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Represents a serialized wrapper function call.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00624" /><CodeLine lineNumber="624"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Serializing calls themselves allows us to batch them: We can make one</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00625" /><CodeLine lineNumber="625"><Highlight kind="comment">/// &quot;run-wrapper-functions&quot; utility and send it a list of calls to run.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00626" /><CodeLine lineNumber="626"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00627" /><CodeLine lineNumber="627"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The motivating use-case for this API is JITLink allocation actions, where</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00628" /><CodeLine lineNumber="628"><Highlight kind="comment">/// we want to run multiple functions to finalize linked memory without having</Highlight></CodeLine>
